---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Spectators"
  description="Guidelines for spectators at DnD Day - Operation Golden Sword. Watch legends being made."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <p class="section-title">The Event</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">For Spectators</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Welcome to Operation Golden Sword. You're here to witness legends being made.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Expectations -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <p class="section-title">What to Expect</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display">
            <span class="gold-gradient">This Is Live</span>
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">ðŸŽ²</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-3">Unscripted Adventure</h3>
              <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
                What you're about to witness is a live tabletop roleplaying game. Nothing is
                scripted. The dice are real, the decisions are made in the moment, and the
                outcomes are genuinely uncertain.
              </p>
              <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Players will debate tactics, stumble over rules, make questionable choices,
                and occasionally roll terribly at the worst possible moment. That's not a
                bugâ€”it's the magic of tabletop gaming.
              </p>
              <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Some moments will be triumphant. Others will be chaotic. All of them will be real.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Golden Rule -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <p class="section-title">The Golden Rule</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display">
            <span class="gold-gradient">Watch, Don't Play</span>
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-dnd-primary/10 border-dnd-primary mb-8">
          <p class="text-dnd-text text-lg text-center font-display">
            You're here to witness legends being made, not to coach them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="text-green-500">âœ“</span> Absolutely Fine
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-dnd-text-muted">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-green-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Talking quietly with other spectators</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-green-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Asking questions about what's happening (to spectators, not players mid-turn)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-green-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Laughing, gasping, cheering, or groaning at dramatic moments</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-green-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Enjoying the chaos</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500">âœ—</span> Please Avoid
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-dnd-text-muted">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-red-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Suggesting strategy or tactics to players</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-red-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Explaining or correcting rules</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-red-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Pointing out things players missed</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-red-500">â€¢</span>
                <span>Commenting on what players "should" do</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-dnd-text-muted/30">
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="text-dnd-text">The exception:</strong> If a DM specifically asks
              for your input or invites you to help with something, you're welcome to engage.
              Otherwise, let the players own their adventureâ€”victories, mistakes, and all.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Moving Between Tables -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <p class="section-title">Four Theaters</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display">
            <span class="gold-gradient">Moving Between Tables</span>
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">ðŸš¶</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-3">Freedom to Roam</h3>
              <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Operation Golden Sword features four simultaneous theaters of war. You're
                welcome to move between tables to catch different parts of the action.
                Each table tells its own story, and together they form the complete battle.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="card text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-3 block">ðŸš«</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary text-lg mb-2">Don't Hover</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Find a spot to watch or move on. Standing directly behind players can be distracting.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-3 block">ðŸ¤«</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary text-lg mb-2">Don't Interrupt</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Slip in and out quietly. Wait for natural breaks if you want to ask someone a question.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-3 block">ðŸ”’</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary text-lg mb-2">Don't Share Intel</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              What happens at one table stays at that table. No carrying information between theaters.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Want to Play Instead?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        There may still be spots available. Sign up to join the action.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Sign Up to Play</a>
        <a href="/event" class="btn btn-secondary">Event Details</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
